Several here have missed my point about Uri Blumenthal, IBM, and
RSA.

Blumenthal is certainly entitled to his opinion.

Often here, though, some post opinions in a context which makes
them appear quasi-factual, usually by association with a seemingly
logical set of phrases.

In the instant case, a lot of very smart people at IBM (and
elsewhere) trust RSA. Thus Blumenthal's statement that he
doesn't deserves no more weight than any other expression of
